[title]de_dust_p3[/title]

Continue with my project. Today, I release my new map, named de_dust_p3 (p1 and p2 can be found in my sub list). With this time releasing, I also learned how to use hint/skip tool and their usefulness. But there may be some problems. If found, leave me comments below :)

[b][u]Features:[/u][/b]
1. Up to 64 players
2. Palm tree/ Skybox
3. Sound/Ambience
4. Fog map
5. 2 Bomb Sites
6. Reducing lag for busy servers
7. Radar included
Hope people enjoy it. Any ideas, leave comments. By the way, vote it :D :p

[title]De_dust_p2[/title]
-------------

Well. After a few weeks learning hard, I had one-week holiday. So come back with happy mapping, my fav work
This map is in my project "making with dust style". I still continue learning all source mapping features and creativity. This time, it's smaller than de_dust_p1, however, not square map.

[b]Feature:[/b]
1. 3D skybox
2. Fog
3. Ambience
4. Bird flying effect (make flying path smoother)
5. Wind
6. Support up to 64 player
7. Fairly high FPS (I think)

Hope people enjoy it. Please comment and vote for me

This map is an extended version of valves de_dust. The reason i did this was because valves dust gave a campfest and didnt support enough players. Because i extended the map it now easily handles 64 players while allowing the T's to plant the bomb often enough also. The map has working overviews and a nav file. The following features are added: - A side route above the bridge. - A sewer leading to a garage in site A. - The sewer also has an exit inside a buildings between site A and B. - A side route at the bridge (sewer also ends here). - A side route in the temple. - And some tiny gameplay changes. - Redone HDR Note: Since the map is extended lower player counts could give some unbalance or make the map feel empty Map is done by me (Alias |UKCS|) Overview is done by Nelsaidi (aka. LG |UKCS|) Beta testing is supported by UKCS (special thanks to TC and LD for making it possible)
